<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Fox</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-18"><hi rend="italic">May 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>For your guidance I quote the following telegram now to be sent to the
                            legation at Lima and communicated to the Argentine and Brazilian
                            Governments (supra).</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
